race.comment: CHASING COLTON (4) doesn't boast the best winning strike rate but ran a strong race last time out, finishing fourth and beaten only 2.5 lengths over 1308m at Timonium (Dirt) after being in the firing line on the corner. Has the ability to take this out. CONTRIVANCE (5) was out of the money two runs back then again missed the frame last start when he got a long way back over 1006m at Colonial Downs, beaten 6 lengths into seventh. Finds a more suitable contest and can find winning form. MO JOKE (1) was prominent at the bend and ran a better race last start to finish a close second over 1308m at this track after missing the placings at the previous appearance. Meeting a deeper field this time but he deserves plenty of thought. SACKETT (7) has been out of the winner's list for a long time, last start finishing fifth at Colonial Downs (Dirt) over 1609m. Finds the right race this time and can find winning form again.
